TITLE: Implementing Registration Schema Validation with Zod in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This schema defines validation rules for user registration data, including email format validation, minimum password length, and confirmation password matching. It uses the Zod library for type-safe schema validation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/feature-sliced/documentation/blob/master/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-docs/current/guides/examples/auth.md#2025-04-19_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { z } from "zod";

export const registrationData = z.object({
    email: z.string().email(),
    password: z.string().min(6),
    confirmPassword: z.string(),
}).refine((data) => data.password === data.confirmPassword, {
    message: "Passwords do not match",
    path: ["confirmPassword"],
});
```

