TITLE: Theme Switching Hook Implementation
DESCRIPTION: Custom React hook that manages theme switching functionality between light and dark modes. Updates document body classes to reflect the current theme.
SOURCE: https://github.com/feature-sliced/documentation/blob/master/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-docs/current/guides/examples/page-layout.md#2025-04-19_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export function useThemeSwitcher() {
  const [theme, setTheme] = useState("light");

  function toggleTheme() {
    setTheme(theme === "light" ? "dark" : "light");
  }

  useEffect(() => {
    document.body.classList.remove("light", "dark");
    document.body.classList.add(theme);
  }, [theme]);

  return [theme, toggleTheme] as const;
}
```

